## Combat Manager Refactor
Now that mobs have a Commander that can execute commands, consider dissolving the combat
manager into per-actor tick behavior:
- Move threat tables onto ActorInstance (each actor tracks who they're fighting and threat levels)
- On tick, each actor in combat checks their threat table and executes combat abilities
  through their commander/handler, just like they execute movement commands for wandering
- The combat manager's orchestration (pairing combatants, running auto_use, publishing
  room messages) moves into the actor tick
- This makes mobs and players symmetrical — both are just actors with a tick that
  execute commands. The only difference is who issues the commands (AI vs player input).
- Eliminates SetAbilityHandler wiring and the separate combat tick phase

## Mob Wandering
- wanderChance and scavengeChance consts in zone.go should be configurable, either per-zone or global config
- Mobs without stay_zone can't currently wander across zone boundaries because tryWander only
  looks up rooms in its own zone instance. Needs access to the full instances map to resolve
  cross-zone exits.

## Consider
- Should overhealing generate threat? Currently heal threat is based on the full heal amount, even if the target is already at max HP.
- Make threat multiplier configurable per effect. Currently damage generates 1:1 threat and heal generates 0.5x threat, both hardcoded. A config field (e.g. "threat_multiplier") would allow tuning per ability.
- TimedPerkCaches in world/zone/room currently apply to all players and no mobs

